<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 02 at 1:18AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...LIGHT SNOW CONTINUES THROUGH THE MID MORNING HOURS...
Widespread light snow will continue through the mid-morning hours
with temperatures now in the low to mid 20s. A slight uptick in
snowfall rates remains possible as colder air filters into the
region, with rates around a quarter inch per hour, and up to a
half inch per hour. Reductions in visibilities with new snowfall
is expected as untreated roadways remain snow covered. Drivers are
urged to exercise caution through the overnight hours.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
